      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(logging): prune non-idle stale diagnostic session states",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n`pruneDiagnosticSessionStates()` in `src/logging/diagnostic-session-state.ts` only deletes entries where `state === \"idle\"` AND `queueDepth <= 0` AND `age > SESSION_STATE_TTL_MS` (30 min). Entries that never transition back to `\"idle\"` — such as recovery-failed sessions — accumulate in the `diagnosticSessionStates` Map indefinitely, holding activity snapshots, tool call history, and queue metadata in V8 heap.\n\nThis PR adds a fallback deletion condition that prunes **any** stale entry exceeding the TTL, regardless of its state. Idle cleanup behavior is unchanged.\n\nFixes #91697\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/logging/diagnostic-session-state.ts`**: In `pruneDiagnosticSessionStates()`, add an `else if` fallback that deletes any entry whose `age > SESSION_STATE_TTL_MS`, not just idle entries with empty queues. 1 file, +4 lines.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Non-idle diagnostic session state entries (e.g. recovery-failed sessions in `\"processing\"` or `\"waiting\"` state) accumulate indefinitely because the prune function only cleans up `\"idle\"` entries. After the fix, any entry exceeding the 30-minute TTL is pruned regardless of state.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Node v22.22.0, Linux 4.19.112-2.el8.x86_64, openclaw commit ebd557ac5a. tsx v4.22.3 used from within the openclaw repo.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n1. Wrote proof script at `scripts/proof-91697.mjs` that imports the real `pruneDiagnosticSessionStates`, `diagnosticSessionStates`, and `resetDiagnosticSessionStateForTest` from `src/logging/diagnostic-session-state.js`\n2. Script populates the process-local Map with 4 entries at different ages and states:\n   - `idle-stale` (idle, 31min old) — should be pruned (existing behavior)\n   - `processing-stale` (processing, 32min old) — should be pruned (NEW behavior)\n   - `processing-fresh` (processing, 10min old) — should survive\n   - `waiting-stale` (waiting, 33min old) — should be pruned (NEW behavior)\n3. Ran `npx tsx scripts/proof-91697.mjs` from the openclaw repo root\n\n**Evidence after fix (terminal capture):**\n\n```\n$ npx tsx scripts/proof-91697.mjs\n\n============================================================\ndiagnostic session state prune — non-idle staleness proof\n============================================================\nnow  = 2026-06-09T12:00:00.000Z\nTTL  = 30 minutes\n\n--- Before prune ---\ntotal entries: 4\n  idle-stale: state=idle age=31min\n  processing-stale: state=processing age=32min\n  processing-fresh: state=processing age=10min\n  waiting-stale: state=waiting age=33min\n\n--- After prune ---\ntotal entries: 1\n  processing-fresh: state=processing age=10min — PRESERVED\n\n--- Verification ---\nidle stale pruned:        ✓\nprocessing stale pruned:   ✓\nwaiting stale pruned:      ✓\nprocessing fresh preserved: ✓\n\n✓ All checks passed.\nexit code: 0\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** Before fix: only `idle-stale` would be pruned; `processing-stale` and `waiting-stale` would survive forever. After fix: all 3 stale entries are pruned (idle, processing, and waiting), while the fresh processing entry (10 min old) is correctly preserved. The fallback `else if` condition ensures non-idle ghost entries cannot accumulate past the 30-minute TTL.\n\n**What was not tested:** Gateway restart with accumulated ghost entries, interaction with `stuckSessionAbortMs` recovery path, full stuck-session recovery lifecycle.\n",
        "branch": "fix/91697-prune-non-idle-diagnostic-states",
